Class JAnnotatedClass

java.lang.Object
com.sun.codemodel.JType
com.sun.codemodel.JClass
org.jsonschema2pojo.model.JAnnotatedClass
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.sun.codemodel.JGenerable, Comparable<com.sun.codemodel.JType>
public class JAnnotatedClass extends com.sun.codemodel.JClass
Represents a type with type-use annotations (Java 8+, JSR 308).

This class wraps a JClass and adds type-use annotations that are rendered directly before the type name. This enables generating code like: 

 List<@Valid Item>
 Map<String, @Nullable Object>

Type-use annotations vs declaration annotations:

  • JAnnotatable.annotate(Class) adds annotations to declarations (the field, method, or class itself). Example: @NotNull private List<String> items;
  • annotated(Class) creates a new type with embedded annotations. Example: private List<@NotNull String> items;
The implementation of this feature relies on reflection and hooking into the JAnnotationUse to access a package-private constructor. This helps us to avoid a breaking change and forking codemodel, but may be a fragile approach.
